Author: obviouslynotjackie
Text: Ahh, thank you! Yeah she isn’t exactly an eating disorder expert but she’s helpful 🤷🏻‍♀️ Again, thank you sm!

Author: kittenwarlock
Text: You’re correct according to the DSM-V. If you like your therapist then it doesn’t really matter as long as they’re aware of your compensatory behaviors but if it concerns you bring it up with them. Things change with diagnosing (and it sounds like it’s not an official diagnosis anyway?), it’s a relatively new disorder in the DSM and not every therapist is an eating disorder expert.
